て修正。計画段階でより慎重にドメインロジック検証 |\n    40→| ruff B017 (blind Exception catch in Task 12) | Plan used `pytest.raises(Exception)` | Use specific exceptions (ValidationError) in frozen model tests |\n    41→| Import sorting on every commit | ruff I001 import order enforcement | Let pre-commit auto-fix handle this; always run `ruff check --fix` before commit |\n    42→\n    43→### 学び\n    44→- Worktree-based parallelism is highly effective for independent file-creation tasks\n    45→- 7 waves for 13 tasks reduced wall-clock time by ~50% vs sequential\n    46→- Plans with domain-specific logic should be verified against actual code before treating test assertions as ground truth\n    47→"}]},"uuid":"bb2959e1-c10e-4bc0-b81a-ea3120bfb739","timestamp":"2026-03-01T20:11:46.306Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/toguchi/PARA/Projects/Private/dynamic-sanmei/.claude/pdca/cycle-20260301-220000.md","content":"# PDCA Cycle: Meishiki Module Implementation\n\n- Status: completed\n- Created: 2026-03-01T22:00:00+09:00\n- Updated: 2026-03-01T23:00:00+09:00\n- Plan: docs/plans/2026-03-01-meishiki-plan.md\n- Design: docs/plans/2026-03-01-meishiki-design.md\n\n## Execution Strategy\n\nWaves based on dependency analysis:\n- Wave 1 (parallel): Tasks 1, 2, 3 — Independent domain enums/models ✅\n- Wave 2 (parallel): Tasks 4, 5, 6, 9 — Tables, protocol, tenchuusatsu calc ✅\n- Wave 3: Task 7 — StandardSchool ✅\n- Wave 4 (parallel): Tasks 8, 10 — Registry + Major Star Calc ✅\n- Wave 5: Task 11 — Subsidiary Star Calc ✅\n- Wave 6: Task 12 — MeishikiCalculator Facade ✅\n- Wave 7: Task 13 — Public API & Quality Gate ✅\n\n## Results\n\n- All 13 tasks completed\n- 234 tests pass (67 existing + 167 new)\n- 99% code coverage\n- Lint: clean, Typecheck: clean\n- 0 Adjust iterations needed\n\n## Retrospective\n\n### 成功\n- Parallel worktree execution worked flawlessly for independent tasks (Waves 1, 2, 4)\n- TDD strictly followed: every task had red→green verification\n- Pre-commit hooks caught import ordering issues automatically\n- Dependency analysis was accurate — no merge conflicts\n\n### 失敗と再発防止\n| 失敗 | 根本原因 | 再発防止策 |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Plan had incorrect test assertion (Task 10: 丙 vs 壬 = 財星, not 官星) | 五行関係の計算ミス in plan doc | サブエージェントが独自検証して修正。計画段階でより慎重にドメインロジック検証 |\n| ruff B017 (blind Exception catch in Task 12) | Plan used `pytest.raises(Exception)` | Use specific exceptions (ValidationError) in frozen model tests |\n| Import sorting on every commit | ruff I001 import order enforcement | Let pre-commit auto-fix handle this; always run `ruff check --fix` before commit |\n\n### 学び\n- Worktree-based parallelism is highly effective for independent file-creation tasks\n- 7 waves for 13 tasks reduced wall-clock time by ~50% vs sequential\n- Plans with domain-specific logic should be verified against actual code before treating test assertions as ground truth\n","numLines":47,"startLine":1,"totalLines":47}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"969687f2-4431-4622-856a-d1e5102015a2"}
